                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">like Germany after WW2, they printed so much money that was added into the economy the value of the money decreased to such a point it was almost worthless</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I've wondered about how this works in EQ before myself.  It would seem that to keep some semblance of a normal economy, plat would periodically need to be taken out of circulation in the game.  Sure, some of this occurs naturally through players quitting, deleting toons, or simply people hoarding plat in their accounts for whatever reason.  But just as when a country issues new currency they must collect and destroy old paper from banks, it would seem that something like this would almost need to be in place in EQ as well.  Otherwise, with every coin-dropping mob that pops in game the value of currency is steadily declining.
<br />

<br />
My conclusion:  Spend it now!  Every day you hold on to it you get a little less back.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
