                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">My conclusion: Spend it now! Every day you hold on to it you get a little less back.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
In fact, the opposite is true. Over time, more and more [insert ubbah item / spell of choice here] become available through drops. Only in rare"ish" occasions will these items or spells get destroyed because of people quitting, moving server or other causes. Platinum, on the other hand, drains away steadily because people need to buy at least some stuff from vendors. This makes items lose their value in relation to money, over time. In other words, items become cheaper. In yet other words, money becomes more valuable, because you need less of it to buy an item. This is called mudflation. 
<br />

<br />
My conclusion: spend what you need to buy nice stuff, don't worry about what it will be worth 2 months down the line, consider what it is worth to you now.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=345084&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Anaximander's Paraphernalia </a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
