                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I find it very amusing that SOE treats its customers like dirt and now wants us to help them.
<br />

<br />
Remember the problems with cultural metals when the mass enchants first came out?  How many people lost bricks of steel, mithril, <span style="font-style: italic">etc.</span> because SOE refused to say there was a mistake?
<br />

<br />
Remember the problems with Jewelcraft Mastery?  How many of us lost valuable material because SOE wouldn't admit there was a problem?  How many of us inadvertantly cheated our customers when making gem studded chains for the <span style="font-weight: bold">weeks</span> when JCM was broken?
<br />

<br />
Now they want us to help them.  I'd feel a whole lot better if they had established a relationship of trust and sharing ahead of time.
<br />

<br />
I know of a few exploits (and I still have a couple backpacks full of shark meat on a random character somewhere from a previous SOE mistake).  I don't use them, but I'm also not SOE's lap dog.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
