		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><a name="12237"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Entharion</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank8.gif" alt="Beer Slut" title="Beer Slut" border="0" /><br />Beer Slut</div><div align="center"><img src="http://home.tiscali.no/~t-brandr/shadow_face.gif" alt="Avatar" border="0" /></div><br /><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;01 Sep 2003</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;87</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Location:&nbsp;Bergen, Norway</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Unknown</div></td>
                <td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=12237&amp;sid=27edae1cd80ab6b8741b1d7b64c74953#12237"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Tue Dec 09, 2003 8:54 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=12237&amp;sid=27edae1cd80ab6b8741b1d7b64c74953"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">In fact, the opposite is true. Over time, more and more [insert ubbah item / spell of choice here] become available through drops. Only in rare"ish" occasions will these items or spells get destroyed because of people quitting, moving server or other causes. Platinum, on the other hand, drains away steadily because people need to buy at least some stuff from vendors. This makes items lose their value in relation to money, over time. In other words, items become cheaper. In yet other words, money becomes more valuable, because you need less of it to buy an item. This is called mudflation. 
<br />

<br />
My conclusion: spend what you need to buy nice stuff, don't worry about what it will be worth 2 months down the line, consider what it is worth to you now.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Not true, because of several things. First of all, the amount of platinum in the game steadily increases, it does not decrease. The amount of pp that goes to vendors and thus "disappears" (Or not, if it results in an item that has resale value, in which case the pp still stays in the economy in a new form) is FAR lower than the amount that enters the game from mob drops. Consider a normal 65 LDoN adventure nets the group about 1kpp combined. The consider the amount of adventures done each day, and compare the influx of pp to the amount people spend on vendor items. Take into consideration all the other places that drops good cash and vendor trash, and the fact that many of the vendor boughts item can be sold back or to other players, and it's quite easy to see that pp is becoming increasingly plentiful. The plat dupe and such things only makes that worse.
<br />

<br />
When talking about normal items, the balance of item influx versus plat influx decides wether the prices will inflate or deflate. If pp enters the game at a faster rate than the items, the price will inflate, and vice versa. Usually though, items enter the game at a far faster rate, especially in the case of LDoN normal drops, which results in those items (and items they make obsolete) dropping in price. On that point, you are right about that consequences.
<br />

<br />
Then, remember that most of the high-price items atm, namely Ornate and 63+ spells, are disposable. Once they get sold to the person that wants them, they disappear from the economy, while the plat stays. This results in the prices of one-time items as these rising, as more plat becomes available while the supply diminishes. The faster plat enters the economy, and the less such disposable items drop, their price will go up. Example, look at Kunark 55-60 drop spells. Almost noone hunts in those zones anymore, yet many of them are needed for every 55+ character that grows up of the appropriate class. This results in ridiculous things like me paying 10k combined for VoQ and VQ, but still not having Forlorn Deeds because it is 10k on my server. Research has held the price down a bit, or it would have been even higher.
<br />

<br />
Conclusion: At the current state of the game, the price of sellable items from frequently hunted zones (LDoN) will continue to drop, the price of nonobsolete sellable items from less hunted zones will stagnate or inflate, and the price of one-time-use items will inflate at differing rates, depending on how many hunts for them (ie, Kunark spells will keep rising, Ornate may or may not keep rising).
<br />

<br />
This is working off prices from two weeks ago, as the current prices are megainflated because people think Yantis is going to buy them no matter what prices, and thus have no statistical significance.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2212" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.elerion.net/pics/sjhosig.jpg" border="0" /></a><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">
<br />
"Carrot Cake Soup is like the taste of watching girls make out. It has an extraordinary power that oscillates between gentle and overwhelming, between light and dark, between pleasure and more pleasure." - Penny Arcade</span></span></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
