                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sony has admitted several times that they need to find a good money sink. They have tried with spell components and with trade skills. They succeeded a bit with horses and leezards. What they need tho is a dependable recurring thing that people will voluntarily spend money on. There were several times when they could have implemented such a system like with the soulbinders or pay for TP services instead of the PoK stones.
<br />

<br />
My personal favorite idea for soaking up plat would be guildhalls. A building is erected in each town that is the 'GuildHall' It is basically a pocket dungeon just like LDoN that allows ONLY people tagged with your guild tag to enter and allows access to merchants and bankers. However, the merchants are for your guild only so can be stocked with guild only items that you set the prices on. There would be a monthly charge for use of the guild hall.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=750403" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: red"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal">Arcady</span></span></span></a>
